args: After relaying the Commander's\nmessage, I was assigned to\nanother mission in the Empire.
All talk of the Shadewolves—once the\nonly thing on everyone's mind—was\nnow forgotten.
Nor could I obtain any new information\nabout the Commander's whereabouts...
A-are you all right?! You look hurt.
He can't have gone far with those injuries.\nSearch every nook and cranny!
Imperial soldiers?! I need to hide!
...Oh. I guess I'm still hanging onto\nthe letter and stuffed toy he gave me.
Oh. I thought they'd found ME.
He must've passed it off to someone else.\nExpand the search perimeter!
We can't let that information get into\nthe hands of the traitorous prince!
Ah! That poor man must have been\ncarrying a message to the Halidom!
I know what he was going through—\nand I will see his work finished!
Well? Did you find that\nmissing information?
No, but we located a set of footprints\nleading in that direction.
They know this land better than I do.\nIt's only a matter of time now.
Wait, I know you. You were with Victor.
A man gave it to me.\nHe told me to deliver it to you.
I see... It seems I didn't make it in time.\nStill, thank you for protecting\nthe letter in his place.
Let me return the favor by protecting you.
It didn't take long for the prince\nto defeat all of the soldiers.
Afterwards, the two of us were able to\ncarry the messenger back to the Halidom.
Thanks, Noelle. I wouldn't have been able\nto bring him back here without you.
He was on a secret mission to obtain\ninformation on a new fortress the Empire\nis planning to build.
I heard he'd found important info,\nand was on my way to meet him.
But I didn't make it in time to get it from\nhim. And after he risked his life to get it!
Oh, he also gave me this.
I think there's more to it than that.
There's something inside.\nI'll pull open the seam a little.
I never would've thought of hiding it\nlike this. Well spotted, Noelle.
Something felt...off when I touched it\nfor the first time.
And I also thought...a messenger would\nhide important information...just like this.
D-do you know where the Commander—\nI mean, where Victor is?
He said he was leaving on\n＂a journey to move forward.＂
I don't know. But he might come back here\nat some point, so you should try to drop\nin from time to time.
But...he told me never to come back.
Only because he was worried about you\nending up in danger.
If I was in his place, I would have said\nthe same thing, I imagine.
You...really think so? But why would\nhe care about a nobody like me?
If he didn't, he wouldn't have offered\nhimself up to ensure your safety.
I can't swear Victor will come back here,\nbut we DID promise to meet again.
I thought I wouldn't ever be able to see\nhim again. That I mustn't ever see him\nagain.
But if I come here, maybe...
Until then, when I think of something\nI want to say to him, I'll write it down.
That way, I can tell him all of it.\nBecause connecting people is what\nmessengers do!
